Ho-ho-ho! Merry Christmas!

00:31.365 --> 00:32.573
Hey, guys.

00:52.845 --> 00:54.220
- Merry Christmas.
- Thanks.

00:54.304 --> 00:55.388
Hey!

00:55.472 --> 00:58.516
Ladies and gentlemen,
can I have your attention?

00:58.600 --> 01:02.311
This has been our best year ever
thanks to Do-it-All-For-You-Dolly.

01:03.814 --> 01:07.108
And I think we should give
a special thanks to the people

01:07.192 --> 01:09.944
responsible for our
record-breaking sales,

01:10.028 --> 01:13.656
our Midwest marketing
and distribution team,

01:13.741 --> 01:16.367
- Scott Calvin and Susan Perry!
- Yeah!

01:16.452 --> 01:20.830
Let's hear it for 'em! Come on!

01:20.914 --> 01:24.333
Susan, darling, come on up here.
Aren't they adorable?

01:24.418 --> 01:26.210
Say a few words.

01:27.004 --> 01:29.797
Thank you very much.
This was really a team effort.

01:29.882 --> 01:32.550
I would just want to thank every one
of you individually...

01:32.634 --> 01:34.218
But we don't have time for that, do we?

01:35.471 --> 01:37.930
In all seriousness, here at B&R Toys,

01:38.015 --> 01:41.267
we're not just about making
a profit in quality toys.

01:41.351 --> 01:46.272
We're also about families. But our
families aren't here with us right now.

01:46.356 --> 01:48.941
Which is probably why Johnson's
secretary is sitting in his lap.

01:49.109 --> 01:52.779
You guys
have a great party. Have a great year.

01:52.863 --> 01:55.072
Drive safe. Thanks very much.

01:57.951 --> 02:00.328
Aren't they wonderful?

02:03.749 --> 02:05.750
Laura, I was hoping to
catch you before you'd left your house.

02:05.834 --> 02:10.045
I ran real late today.
You wouldn't believe the traffic out here.

02:10.380 --> 02:12.632
Yeah, same to you!

02:12.716 --> 02:15.384
And that's not very ladylike!

02:15.469 --> 02:18.262
Anyway, I'll try to get
to my house as soon as I can.

02:18.347 --> 02:20.014
Oh. There's the problem right there.

02:20.098 --> 02:23.476
Three car pileup.
I'm really gonna be late.

02:23.560 --> 02:25.645
Hark, carol bells, sweet silver bells

02:25.729 --> 02:27.814
All seem to sing, throw cares away

02:27.898 --> 02:29.982
Christmas is here bringing good cheer

02:30.067 --> 02:32.068
To young and old, meek and the bold

02:32.152 --> 02:34.195
Ding dong and dong, balance in song

02:34.279 --> 02:36.239
Ring joyful ring, all caroling

02:36.323 --> 02:38.241
One seems to hear
Words of good cheer

02:38.325 --> 02:40.409
From everywhere, filling the air

02:40.536 --> 02:42.453
Oh, how they pound, raising the sound

02:42.538 --> 02:44.580
Go hand in hand, calling in the town

02:44.665 --> 02:46.541
Gaily they ring while people sing

02:46.625 --> 02:48.709
Songs of good cheer
Christmas is here

02:48.794 --> 02:52.839
Merry, merry, merry, merry Christmas

02:52.923 --> 02:54.841
On we will sing, dawn with a hymn

02:54.925 --> 02:57.009
Angel will come to every home

02:57.094 --> 02:59.011
Hark, carol bells, sweet silver bells

02:59.096 --> 03:01.055
All seem to sing, throw cares away

03:01.139 --> 03:03.015
Hark, carol bells, sweet silver bells

03:03.100 --> 03:05.184
One seems to hear
